headlines.description: Dewan Huell scored 15 points, Lonnie Walker IV had 13 and No. 6 Miami used a fast start to beat George Washington 59-50 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 6 Miami remains undefeated, downs GW 59-50

headlines.description: Keenan Evans scored 13 points, Zhaire Smith added 12 and No. 24 Texas Tech beat Rice 73-53 on Saturday night in the Red Raiders' first game since 1999 at Lubbock Municipal Coliseum, their old home court.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 24 Texas Tech rolls past Rice 73-53 on old home court

headlines.description: Justin Mitchell scored 18 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for his first double-double of the season and Wright State beat Toledo 77-69 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell's double-double helps Wright St beat Toledo 77-69

headlines.description: Jaylen Shaw scored 23 points, Zac Cuthbertson finished with 22 and the two combined to shoot 14 of 20 from the field as Coastal Carolina beat NAIA Montreat College 83-70 on Saturday.
Simi Socks scored 20 points with eight rebounds and Incarnate Word beat Missouri-Kansas City 77-73 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Socks with 20 points leads Incarnate Word over UMKC 77-73

headlines.description: Rickey Holden scored 16 points, including two free throws with 10 seconds left, and CSU Bakersfield beat Georgia Southern 55-53 on Saturday night to win its third straight.
headlines.shortLinkText: CSU Bakersfield beats Georgia Southern 55-53 behind Holden

headlines.description: Hunter Crist came off the Green Bay bench to hit 6 of 7 shots from the field, including both 3-point attempts, to fuel the Phoenix' 86-50 romp past Division II Wisconsin-Parkside on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green Bay routs Div. II Wisconsin Parkside early, wins 86-50

headlines.description: Justin James had 21 points and 12 rebounds and Wyoming pulled away in the final minute to beat winless Texas Southern 72-66 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Justin James leads Wyoming over Texas Southern 72-66

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "Im getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. Its a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how Im going to dictate how my team wins.  Its a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... Its a process. Right now, its tough."
